1
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,000
Yiran's mom

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:35,800
Actually,

3
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:39,800
many of our town officials are young people,

4
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,920
and lots of them aren't even locals.

5
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:44,560
Every family has its own struggles.

6
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:49,280
You were just asking me earlier,

7
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,640
I'm a mother too, right?

8
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,000
We both have kids.

9
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:54,200
But what I want to tell you is,

10
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:56,160
as mothers,

11
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:58,000
we must respect our kids' choices, right?

12
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:58,560
Respect their choices, okay?

13
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:02,240
You're back.

14
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:05,000
We just finished up, Secretary.

15
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,560
Went out to the ditches.

16
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,760
County environmental inspectors came today.

17
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,400
Alright.

18
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:10,240
Yiran,

19
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,720
do your job well,

20
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,640
and take good care of your mom too.

21
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:17,800
Mom.

22
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,880
Wait, what are you even doing here?

23
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:20,240
Go back.

24
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:20,880
Auntie.

25
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:21,680
Go home.

26
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,440
I didn't...

27
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,320
Auntie.

28
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,120
I'm fine.

29
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:24,920
Yiran, let's go.

30
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:25,960
Have a meal with your mom.

31
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:27,040
Come eat at our cafeteria.

32
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:27,520
I'm not eating.

33
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,840
Our cafeteria food is really good.

34
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:30,440
Today, I'll arrange a special meal for you.

35
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:31,200
I'm really not eating.

36
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,760
Try our cafeteria's cooking.

37
00:02:32,760 --> 00:02:33,960
I said no.

38
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:34,960
Yiran's mom.

39
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,760
The kids are grown now.

40
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:37,840
We've got to let go when it's time.

41
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,040
You...

42
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,800
Can't you slow down a bit?

43
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,280
Slow down. Don't walk away.

44
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,200
When it comes to my work,

45
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,280
can you just stay out of it?

46
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,120
I gave birth to you. Of course I will.

47
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:53,280
Yes, you gave birth to me,

48
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,480
but my work has nothing to do with you.

49
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,200
How is it not? Stop right there!

50
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:00,320
You... stop right there!

51
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:02,920
Everything I do is for your own good.

52
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:04,560
Let me tell you, I'm not like Dad.

53
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,440
I won't be like him,

54
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:06,560
listening to you my whole life.

55
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,760
If your dad had listened to me,

56
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:09,760
he wouldn't be like he is now.

57
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,200
He shouldn't have listened to you.

58
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:12,920
I'm thinking now,

59
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:14,480
if Dad hadn't listened to you back then,

60
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:15,920
maybe nothing would have happened to him.

61
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:22,080
What kind of talk is that?

62
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,200
Doesn't everyone have their own fate?

63
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:25,640
Yes,

64
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:26,640
everyone has their own fate.

65
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,080
Mom, from now on,

66
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,400
whether you like it or not,

67
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,480
my fate is mine to handle.

68
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:31,760
It's got nothing to do with you.

69
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,920
What do you mean it's not my business?

70
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:33,840
Stop right there!

71
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:34,920
Explain yourself!

72
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:37,000
I birthed you, how is it not my business?

73
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:38,760
I have to be involved in all your affairs.

74
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,000
How could I possibly not?

75
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:52,080
I gave up the job I loved most.

76
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,920
I worked myself to the bone,

77
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,960
earning every penny I could,

78
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,520
just to pay for my mom's treatment.

79
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:01,480
I feel like I gave her

80
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,480
the best of everything I had.

81
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,960
At least I did my best.

82
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:10,200
But nothing ever seems to satisfy her.

83
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:14,480
I don't know if I should say this,

84
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:15,240
but...

85
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,360
what if my dad, back then,

86
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,920
hadn't worked so desperately for money,

87
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:24,480
hadn't tried so hard to earn more

88
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,880
just to make my mom happy,

89
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,440
hadn't been

90
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,800
driving day and night...

91
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:37,360
maybe he wouldn't have had that accident.

92
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,680
Don't cry.

93
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,880
It's not your fault.

94
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:50,600
Tell you what,

95
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,800
don't see her for now.

96
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,160
Whatever comes up, tell me.

97
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,400
I'll help you handle it, okay?

98
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,120
Don't cry anymore.

99
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,120
It's okay, it's okay.

100
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,440
A single sheet of thin Xuan paper

101
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:20,800
goes through hundreds of steps,

102
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:23,040
carrying a millennium of culture.

103
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:26,040
Where does our cultural confidence lie?

104
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,120
It comes from the precious heritage

105
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:30,040
our ancestors left behind.

106
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,640
To cherish these precious treasures,

107
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:34,880
we can't simply place them

108
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,480
on an altar to be worshipped.

109
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:38,160
Instead, we must find ways

110
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:40,640
to integrate them into the times,

111
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:43,480
and further into the daily lives

112
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:44,800
of ordinary people.

113
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:45,960
Today,

114
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:47,680
with all the leaders present,

115
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,360
I'd like to make three points.

116
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:54,280
Industry needs bold, sweeping strokes.

117
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:57,600
Boldly drive cultural-tourism integration.

118
00:05:57,920 --> 00:06:01,400
Actively develop study and heritage tours.

119
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:04,640
Launch more cultural products and models.

120
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,440
Let traditional culture, in this new era,

121
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,360
show new charm and shine anew.

122
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,120
When innovating,

123
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:14,960
we need patience like scroll restoration.

124
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:17,320
"Hold fast to the green mountain,

125
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:19,480
with roots planted firmly in broken rock."

126
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:22,720
Developing new paper, crafts, and products

127
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,280
requires the careful work of embroidery.

128
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,920
Once we lock onto the right direction,

129
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:29,560
we must be prepared for the long haul,

130
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,680
pushing on until the very end.

131
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:34,760
Third point:

132
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:39,720
Development needs a holistic vision.

133
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,840
The Four Treasures are inseparable.

134
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,440
Don't just talk about Xuan paper alone.

135
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:47,760
Link paper, ink, brush, and inkstone.

136
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:50,800
With Xuan brushes, Hui ink, She inkstones,

137
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:53,600
build interconnection and shared growth,

138
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:56,440
a vision where each supports the other.

139
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,040
The Provincial Committee deeply cares about

140
00:07:02,040 --> 00:07:04,440
Xuan paper heritage and its development.

141
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:07,200
Our superiors expect us to take action.

142
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:08,560
Secretary Chen,

143
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,320
Secretary Peng,

144
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,640
I suggest you break out of local thinking.

145
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,880
Broaden your perspective.

146
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,240
Be even bolder.

147
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,640
Plan innovation with a big-picture view.

148
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:22,440
The province and the city will support you,

149
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,120
and serve as your strong backing.

150
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:24,920
Yes.

151
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,200
Deputy Mayor Qin, rest assured,

152
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:27,440
we will

153
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:29,800
put this into action as soon as possible.

154
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:30,680
Please rest assured.

155
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:31,800
Good.

156
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:33,760
Come, this way please.

157
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,680
I think the leaders are right.

158
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,680
Look at these past two years.

159
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:52,240
In our work on the Xuan paper industry,

160
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,800
we've truly been too conservative.

161
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,560
Changes in industry development

162
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,320
follow normal economic patterns.

163
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:59,200
But we can't just sit around waiting.

164
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,680
We should take proactive action, right?

165
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,200
Yes, yes, we need to come up with

166
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,000
some proactive measures.

167
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,680
The Xuan Paper Culture Festival

168
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:10,560
we held a couple years ago was great.

169
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:11,680
We can keep doing it.

170
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:15,440
Culture sets the stage, economy performs.

171
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:16,120
Right.

172
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,440
The key issue is,

173
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:21,160
the stage is easy to set up now,

174
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,560
but the show is hard to perform.

175
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,920
We held the Xuan Paper Festival before.

176
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,280
Why did we stop?

177
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:30,240
The scene was grand and lively,

178
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,200
but the actual results were limited.

179
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:35,280
These past two years, we finally opened up

180
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:38,799
the Wannianhong and wallpaper markets.

181
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,880
The industry's showing some improvement.

182
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:45,720
Everyone wants to protect the business

183
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:47,080
and develop steadily.

184
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,440
Nobody wants to do meaningless things.

185
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:51,320
How is it meaningless?

186
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:54,440
If it's meaningless, we didn't do it right.

187
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:57,120
If we didn't, we should learn from it.

188
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,080
Director Liao, what era do we live in now?

189
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:03,880
We must leverage this social media era

190
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:06,080
so more people can know, understand,

191
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,240
and love our Xuan paper.

192
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,320
So,

193
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:09,920
in my personal opinion,

194
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,160
this work must be done,

195
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,360
and done as soon as possible.

196
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,560
This will be our next priority.

197
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:16,560
So, Director Liao,

198
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:18,560
The Economic Development Office gets this.

199
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,880
Get it done as soon as possible, alright?

200
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:21,880
Secretary Peng,

201
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:24,440
I'm not just making it up when I say no.

202
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,680
I've spoken with many in the industry.

203
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:28,360
What I'm saying reflects public opinion.

204
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:31,200
If you force this assignment on me,

205
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:32,240
and it goes wrong,

206
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:34,400
it could cause real trouble.

207
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:36,520
That's why I'm telling you to do it well.

208
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,320
Work hard and do it right.

209
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,560
Not everything works out just by trying hard.

210
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:44,240
If it fails, we're just asking for trouble,

211
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,640
becoming a laughingstock.

212
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,120
Director Liao,

213
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,120
for a lot of things,

214
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:54,000
anticipating difficulties is a good thing.

215
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:56,360
But don't always shy away from challenges.

216
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:59,840
Remember, plan well and you'll succeed.

217
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:01,800
So that's settled.

218
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:02,960
This matter

219
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,240
gets handled immediately.

220
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:07,240
Get me a feasibility report

221
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,440
as soon as possible.

222
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:09,400
Tomorrow.

223
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,440
I want it by tomorrow.

224
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:11,560
We can write the report,

225
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:13,040
but whether it's feasible or not

226
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,000
depends on the actual situation.

227
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:17,680
I want a feasibility report,

228
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,320
not an infeasibility report.

229
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,080
Holding a cultural festival is a good thing.

230
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:26,040
Why write a report saying it's not feasible?

231
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,840
Who told you it was a good thing?

232
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:31,160
You have to go with the flow.

233
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:33,200
Act at the right time.

234
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:35,680
Everyone wants to celebrate Spring Festival.

235
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:39,200
But who celebrates on Tomb-Sweeping Day?

236
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:40,320
Director Liao,

237
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:42,200
that's not a fair comparison.

238
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,920
The provincial leaders just came for research

239
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:46,600
and fully expressed their support

240
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,800
for the Xuan paper industry's development.

241
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:48,440
What's more,

242
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,040
this...

243
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:50,480
Holding a Xuan paper cultural festival now

244
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,440
is the perfect timing.

245
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:53,080
We saw the Publicity livestream too,

246
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:53,800
right?

247
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:56,400
Did the provincial leaders say to hold a festival?

248
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:57,920
Which sentence said that?

249
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:58,920
Where did they say it?

250
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,160
When did they say it?

251
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:01,920
Don't use their name as a shield.

252
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:02,960
Let me tell you, Lin Yiran,

253
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,320
young people need to be honest,

254
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,280
down-to-earth,

255
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:07,800
and base everything on reality.

256
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:09,560
Wait,

257
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:12,560
how is a festival not down-to-earth?

258
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:14,600
How is it not based on reality?

259
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,560
When it comes to hosting large events,

260
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:19,560
I have plenty of experience.

261
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:21,960
You must be cautious, cautious,

262
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,160
and cautious again.

263
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,200
On the surface, it looks lively and exciting,

264
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:28,320
but in the end, there's no real benefit,

265
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,480
not a shred of economic return.

266
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,440
Then what will you do?

267
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:32,280
Then we find a way to make the festival

268
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:34,320
bring benefits to everyone.

269
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:38,040
If things were as simple as you think,

270
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,200
why has our cultural festival

271
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,800
been on hold for so many years?

272
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:43,720
Are we all idiots just waiting to die?

273
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:44,960
And only you're clever?

274
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:45,920
No,

275
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:48,520
that's why I wrote a proper report.

276
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:50,680
Doing it gives us hope of success.

277
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:52,600
Not doing it means no hope at all.

278
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,000
Don't be angry, Director Liao.

279
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,040
Please, don't be upset.

280
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,560
The thing is,

281
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:01,160
we've never done an infeasibility report.

282
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:02,440
If it's not feasible, just don't do it.

283
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:04,080
Why bother writing a report?

284
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,800
Because the leadership requires it.

285
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,040
Is that reason good enough?

286
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:12,320
I just don't think the leaders

287
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,160
would ask for an infeasibility report.

288
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,240
What do you mean, you don't believe me?

289
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,200
Aren't I your boss?

290
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,440
Wasn't I clear enough?

291
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,560
Yes, you're my boss,

292
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:22,040
and you were perfectly clear.

293
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,600
I just feel it shouldn't be...

294
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,720
I don't care what you feel.

295
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,200
It's what I feel that matters.

296
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:27,960
Just write it the way I said.

297
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:30,720
This...

298
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,320
Is he even being reasonable?

299
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:54,920
Finished writing it?

300
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,840
You look like you didn't sleep all night.

301
00:12:58,760 --> 00:12:59,840
I took a nap.

302
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,080
An infeasibility report.

303
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,240
Just list out the reasons

304
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:05,280
why it's not feasible.

305
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:06,440
Is it really that complicated?

306
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,040
But you know,

307
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:13,240
it felt more feasible the more I wrote.

308
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,600
And extremely feasible at that.

309
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,400
Looks to me like

310
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:23,200
you wrote a feasibility report.

311
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,040
Where's Director Liao now?

312
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:28,080
On the back hill.

313
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:30,680
With the EPA inspecting the cleanup.

314
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:35,080
Don't tell me you're planning to...

315
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,440
If anything goes wrong, it's not on you.

316
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,320
I'll take the heat.

317
00:13:38,040 --> 00:13:39,840
Sis, I'm begging you.

318
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:40,360
Forget it.

319
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:41,240
If you pull a stunt like this,

320
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:42,640
none of us will get any peace.

321
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:43,880
I'm used to it already.

322
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:45,320
Let him yell if he wants to.

323
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:47,280
The work still has to get done, right?

324
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:48,320
I've got things to do.

325
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,560
You're on your own. Good luck.

326
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:02,920
Hello?

327
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:04,440
Director.

328
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:06,160
Um, I sent you the report.

329
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:07,800
I'm busy right now.

330
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:08,600
We'll talk when I get back.

331
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,440
Well, Director Ge is already pushing for it.

332
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:13,200
He says Secretary Peng is waiting to review it.

333
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:14,960
I've got farsightedness.

334
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:16,040
Can't read the words on my phone.

335
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,040
You know that perfectly well.

336
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:21,000
Then I'll let Director Ge know

337
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,320
to show Secretary Peng when you're back.

338
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,240
Lin Yiran.

339
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:26,360
Are you deliberately trying to give me trouble?

340
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:28,880
You wrote it the way I told you, right?

341
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:29,920
Then go ahead and send it over.

342
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:43,840
Excuse me

343
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:44,640
Director Liao is here

344
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:45,240
Come, come

345
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,680
Give Director Liao a round of applause.

346
00:14:46,680 --> 00:14:47,320
Good

347
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,360
Look at that

348
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:55,400
Our veteran comrade is truly a veteran

349
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,480
Real vision

350
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:59,760
Personal grievances aside

351
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:02,760
When it comes to work, he gives it his all

352
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:03,600
Director Liao

353
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:05,440
This spirit is truly commendable

354
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:06,840
Worthy of praise

355
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:11,520
On this point

356
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:13,080
I feel deeply moved as well

357
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:15,840
Director Liao, in character and conduct,

358
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:17,680
has many admirable qualities

359
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:19,800
worth all of us striving to learn from

360
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:21,680
Whether his words are right or wrong

361
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:23,280
he'll always speak his mind

362
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:25,360
Speak up, and we'll all discuss together

363
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,920
Even if there's an issue with his words,

364
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:27,960
it doesn't really matter

365
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:30,160
Because when it comes to implementation

366
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:32,280
we must move in the right direction

367
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:33,880
and work hard at it, right?

368
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:34,600
Exactly, yes, yes, yes

369
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,200
Yes, indeed

370
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,280
Well said, well said

371
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:38,840
Alright, let's get to the main topic

372
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:39,480
Good

373
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:42,280
Today, Director Liao and Lin Yiran

374
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,680
were invited to attend this meeting

375
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:46,040
because we want them to participate

376
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:49,320
in how we'll implement the next steps

377
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:51,240
First, I think their idea of changing

378
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:54,880
Xuan Paper to Four Treasures Festival

379
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:57,280
is a wonderful idea

380
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:58,800
I even specifically

381
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:00,920
reported it to County Secretary Chen

382
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:03,080
and the head of the Propaganda Department

383
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:05,120
They then reported it to higher-ups

384
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:07,120
Now all the leaders

385
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,840
regarding our creative idea

386
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:10,920
have expressed approval and support

387
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:13,040
Deputy Mayor Qin has directed

388
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:15,480
that our hometown of Xuan paper,

389
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:17,080
Peach Blossom Town

390
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:17,880
The county

391
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:20,440
will give us full support and guarantees

392
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,560
Security

393
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:23,600
reception

394
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:24,440
fire safety

395
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:25,120
you know

396
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:27,720
everything, they'll go all out

397
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:31,080
to safeguard our Four Treasures Festival

398
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:32,440
Good

399
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:35,800
What, what?

400
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:37,560
Secretary

401
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,280
Four Treasures Festival?

402
00:16:39,280 --> 00:16:40,520
What's going on here?

403
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:45,880
I thought a Xuan Paper Fest was feasible,

404
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:49,360
but a Four Treasures Festival is even more

405
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:52,080
reckless and audacious

406
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:52,800
Director Liao

407
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,480
please watch your words and behavior

408
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:59,440
You are at an expanded Party meeting.

409
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:01,520
My apologies

410
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:03,560
Secretary Peng, hear me out

411
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:06,079
I've already made my position clear

412
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:09,160
I oppose holding the Xuan Paper Festival

413
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:12,240
A Four Treasures Festival is even crazier.

414
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:14,640
Could our little Peach Blossom Town

415
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:15,720
could ever pull off?

416
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:16,920
It's simply a joke

417
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:17,720
Director Liao

418
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,800
Let me remind you again

419
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:23,000
Our Party committee has approved this.

420
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:25,200
What we're discussing now is

421
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:27,880
how to implement it

422
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:29,960
I

423
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:32,920
refuse to comply

424
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,200
Director Liao

425
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:47,240
You can keep your personal opinions

426
00:17:47,520 --> 00:17:48,560
to yourself.

427
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:50,560
Excuse me,

428
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,160
but please leave the meeting now.

429
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:01,720
Director Liao.

430
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:04,560
Director Liao, Director Liao!

431
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:10,760
Director Liao.

432
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:13,440
Director Liao.

433
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:14,720
I admit

434
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,560
I shouldn't have done this behind your back.

435
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:17,880
I apologize to you.

436
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:19,160
No need for that.

437
00:18:19,680 --> 00:18:22,240
A tiny town of over ten thousand people,

438
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:23,680
what makes you qualified

439
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:25,240
to host a Four Treasures Culture Festival?

440
00:18:25,360 --> 00:18:26,600
When you botch it up

441
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,720
and disappoint all those entrepreneurs,

442
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:30,560
you'll be the one apologizing to them.

443
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:33,440
I believe we can pull this event off.

444
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:34,600
Not "we."

445
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:36,040
It's "you."

446
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,440
Since you're so determined,

447
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:39,920
I'll be ready anytime

448
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,200
to applaud your great achievements.

449
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:44,280
Director Liao.

450
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,680
Wishful thinking.

451
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,440
Director Liao.

452
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:47,800
Yiran.

453
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:50,280
Secretary Peng.

454
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:51,800
It's fine, eat up.

455
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:52,920
No, it's...

456
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:53,720
It's okay.

457
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,240
Eat.

458
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:01,520
Director Liao's not here.

459
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:04,000
He just stepped out to take a call.

460
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:06,840
I've got good news for you.

461
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:09,400
Acting head, Economic Development Office.

462
00:19:09,960 --> 00:19:11,000
The Party committee meeting just wrapped up.

463
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,520
It'll be officially announced in the next few days.

464
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:14,000
Me?

465
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:17,120
They also arranged a new position for Director Liao,

466
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:18,880
called Culture and Tourism Ambassador.

467
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,680
They said it's to make room for you.

468
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:22,280
Director Liao.

469
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:39,400
Director Liao

470
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:41,080
Taozi just told me everything

471
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:42,200
This isn't the outcome I wanted

472
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:43,560
I think it's unfair to you

473
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,600
Cut the act

474
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:50,080
I'm going to see Secretary Peng

475
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,000
Yiran

476
00:19:58,080 --> 00:20:00,000
Putting on quite the full performance

477
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:05,240
I really underestimated you young folks

478
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:06,960
Director

479
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:08,560
Lin Yiran isn't that kind of person

480
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:10,320
Yiran

481
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:22,560
Secretary Peng

482
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:24,520
I don't think this is fair

483
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:25,840
It's unfair to Director Liao

484
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:30,280
Well then

485
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:33,720
Is promoting him to deputy mayor fair?

486
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:36,560
Xiao Lin

487
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:39,520
Personnel decisions aren't child's play.

488
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:42,640
The organization assigns the work

489
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:44,400
The angles we consider

490
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:45,840
are part of that work too

491
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:47,840
If you think it's unfair,

492
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:50,040
then why don't you handle it yourself?

493
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:53,840
Have you been

494
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:56,920
listening to some gossip?

495
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:01,240
They said

496
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:02,760
transferring Director Liao out

497
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:04,040
is to make room for me

498
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:10,080
So what if it's to make room for you?

499
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,080
Making room for you

500
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:16,560
to run the Four Treasures Festival well.

501
00:21:17,040 --> 00:21:20,080
to run Economic Development Office well.

502
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:21,360
If you don't perform,

503
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:23,160
you'll be making room for someone else too

504
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:24,720
The arrangement isn't the issue.

505
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:26,720
But on a personal level,

506
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:27,560
I can't accept it

507
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,760
Personal feelings, I totally understand

508
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:32,280
Of course,

509
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:35,000
if you refuse to obey the organization,

510
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:36,560
write a report

511
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:39,840
and I'll halt the transfer immediately

512
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:42,240
But whether Director Liao stays or goes

513
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:44,280
isn't something you should worry about.

514
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:48,640
Let me tell you, Lin Yiran

515
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:51,840
Just based on what you said to me

516
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,720
in my office today,

517
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:56,840
Director Liao didn't mentor you well.

518
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:58,240
He's been derelict in his duty

519
00:21:58,360 --> 00:21:59,760
Enough, go back now

520
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:01,400
Reflect properly on your own problems

521
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:02,280
I've got things to do

522
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:02,800
That'll be all

523
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:04,360
Come back

524
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:08,280
Go

525
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:10,200
Bring Director Liao to me

526
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:52,280
Yiran

527
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:54,080
Secretary Peng is furious right now.

528
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,000
If you barge in there,

529
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,200
you'll only put Director Liao on the spot.

530
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:56,760
Don't you get it?

531
00:22:58,000 --> 00:22:58,560
Lin Yiran.

532
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,040
Listen to me.

533
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:01,320
This won't solve anything.

534
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:02,200
You'll only make things worse.

535
00:23:02,200 --> 00:23:02,760
Do you understand?

536
00:23:02,760 --> 00:23:04,760
I put these two young women in your hands,

537
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:05,960
and this is how you lead them?

538
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,680
Always shielding and coddling them.

539
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:11,960
Are you trying to raise them

540
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,880
into pampered little princesses?

541
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:15,640
Director Liao,

542
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:18,240
just how are you leading this team?

543
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:20,280
Are you even fit to lead them?

544
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,640
Young people,

545
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:25,040
when there's an opportunity,

546
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:27,120
you have to let them charge ahead.

547
00:23:27,760 --> 00:23:28,840
You have to build up

548
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:30,720
their ability to shoulder responsibility.

549
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:32,920
What's so scary about falling down?

550
00:23:33,280 --> 00:23:34,960
You fall, you get back up.

551
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:36,760
Fall again, get up again.

552
00:23:37,480 --> 00:23:38,480
You've got to shed blood and sweat.

553
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:39,800
Yiran, at this critical moment,

554
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,320
Secretary Peng won't let you leave.

555
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:41,960
Don't go in there and fan the flames.

556
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:43,160
Taozi, let go of me.

557
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:44,520
Read books,

558
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:46,080
tell people history stories every day.

559
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:47,200
Look at our Peach Blossom Town...

560
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:47,680
Secretary Peng.

561
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,000
Can you even lead this team?

562
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:53,920
Secretary Peng,

563
00:23:54,320 --> 00:23:56,440
I'm willing to work on the Four Treasures.

564
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:58,440
No matter how hard, I won't complain.

565
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:00,000
But I just can't take

566
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:01,520
the Economic Development Office acting head.

567
00:24:02,040 --> 00:24:02,920
If that's not acceptable,

568
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:06,480
here's my resignation letter.

569
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:13,960
What are you all standing here for?

570
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:15,360
Have you finished all your work?

571
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:16,320
Di- Director...

572
00:24:16,360 --> 00:24:17,360
Get back to work, now!

573
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:30,880
Lin Yiran,

574
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:32,360
get back inside.

575
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:34,560
Director.

576
00:24:52,280 --> 00:24:53,080
Director.

577
00:24:58,440 --> 00:25:00,000
I remember one of you two

578
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:02,200
wanted to treat me to a meal.

579
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:03,760
I did say that.

580
00:25:03,760 --> 00:25:04,760
I said it too.

581
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:06,560
I've offered many times,

582
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:07,600
but you always stuck to your principles

583
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:08,520
and refused.

584
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:13,960
So today, I'll make an exception.

585
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:16,240
Just a street food stall, nothing fancy.

586
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:20,520
Director.

587
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:33,520
Director, try this.

588
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:35,040
Alright.

589
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:44,160
Pretty tasty.

590
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:46,280
This place grills amazing skewers.

591
00:25:46,280 --> 00:25:48,520
A quarter of my salary goes to them.

592
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:52,280
It's been so long since I had skewers.

593
00:25:53,040 --> 00:25:53,960
The last time I had them

594
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,400
must've been before I got married.

595
00:25:59,120 --> 00:26:00,480
You don't like them?

596
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:02,560
My absolute favorite

597
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:03,640
is barbecue.

598
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:05,960
But you see,

599
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:07,840
my wife

600
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:09,800
and my kid don't like it,

601
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:11,760
so I stopped eating it.

602
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:14,640
At work,

603
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,520
I never accept meal invitations.

604
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:20,600
I always feel that accepting a meal

605
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:21,880
if something comes up later,

606
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:24,640
you can't bring yourself to speak up.

607
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:25,960
You two, eat up too.

608
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:27,480
Dig in.

609
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:29,520
Director,

610
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:30,720
don't drink alone.

611
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:31,640
Here's a toast to you.

612
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,800
I wish you good health

613
00:26:35,840 --> 00:26:36,760
and happiness always.

614
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:39,600
Teacher Liao,

615
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:44,520
I'm not good with words,

616
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:47,680
but I really want to thank you.

617
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:50,880
Thanks for protecting us like a father.

618
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:56,160
I love it when you call me Teacher Liao.

619
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:58,000
Honestly,

620
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:00,320
being a teacher

621
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:02,760
suited me better than being an official.

622
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:05,200
Lin Yiran,

623
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:07,200
I wish you, in your role as

624
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:09,480
acting head, Economic Development Office,

625
00:27:10,120 --> 00:27:11,520
will live up to the mission,

626
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:13,920
achieve great results,

627
00:27:14,520 --> 00:27:17,760
and benefit Peach Blossom Town's people.

628
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:21,000
Director Liao, I...

629
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:23,160
I don't know what I should...

630
00:27:23,760 --> 00:27:24,560
I...

631
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:25,880
Don't say anything.

632
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:29,240
Secretary Peng was right.

633
00:27:31,120 --> 00:27:32,200
You're capable,

634
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:34,120
you want to make a difference,

635
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:36,840
so you deserve a bigger stage

636
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:39,440
to accomplish even more.

637
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:43,000
In my eyes,

638
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:45,120
you two

639
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:47,080
are like my own daughters.

640
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:51,320
I don't want you

641
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,520
to make the same mistakes I made.

642
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,920
I don't want you

643
00:27:58,840 --> 00:28:00,160
to suffer the way I have.

644
00:28:07,120 --> 00:28:08,200
Enough about all that.

645
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:09,480
The days ahead

646
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:11,520
you'll have to walk on your own.

647
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:14,240
Work hard.

648
00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:16,560
Don't be like me.

649
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:18,360
Director.

650
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:20,320
Don't say that.

651
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:22,680
I think you're the most learned person

652
00:28:22,760 --> 00:28:23,880
in all of Peach Blossom Town.

653
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:24,720
That's right.

654
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:26,240
Taozi's absolutely right.

655
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:29,320
You're the only Xuan paper theorist

656
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:30,360
in all of Peach Blossom Town.

657
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:33,560
Stop flattering me.

658
00:28:36,160 --> 00:28:37,240
I know exactly what I'm worth,

659
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:38,880
better than anyone.

660
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:41,800
If they truly put this weight on me,

661
00:28:42,280 --> 00:28:43,840
I couldn't pull it off.

662
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:47,400
At the office,

663
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:49,800
some call me Director Liao,

664
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:52,040
others call me Teacher Liao,

665
00:28:52,520 --> 00:28:54,440
but behind my back, nobody respects me.

666
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:56,560
At home,

667
00:28:58,680 --> 00:29:00,600
my wife thinks I'm a loser.

668
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:07,200
This is just my fate.

669
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:11,200
This is all I'm capable of.

670
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:15,760
Once you reach my age,

671
00:29:18,560 --> 00:29:20,280
you've got to accept your fate.

672
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:22,400
Director.

673
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:24,360
Don't be so discouraged.

674
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,280
What's wrong with being a tourism ambassador?

675
00:29:26,760 --> 00:29:28,520
I think being a tourism ambassador is wonderful.

676
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:31,040
You'd put Peach Blossom Town on the map.

677
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:32,360
What a meaningful thing to do!

678
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:35,000
From now on, the three of us

679
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:36,760
are comrades in the same trench.

680
00:29:37,080 --> 00:29:38,760
Let's join hands and move forward,

681
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:40,600
and create a new era of glory.

682
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:42,520
That's right.

683
00:29:43,040 --> 00:29:44,200
We won't accept fate.

684
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:46,520
No matter where we work,

685
00:29:46,600 --> 00:29:48,680
we'll do the job brilliantly

686
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:50,160
and earn everyone's respect.

687
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:53,160
Now that's what I like to hear.

688
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:57,440
Let's do our jobs well,

689
00:29:58,760 --> 00:30:00,800
and to the future of Peach Blossom Town,

690
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:03,280
cheers!

691
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:06,360
Cheers!

692
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:21,040
No matter how much overtime we put in now,

693
00:30:21,040 --> 00:30:22,040
no matter how many shifts we run,

694
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:23,720
even working 24 hours nonstop,

695
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:24,760
there's no way we can complete

696
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:25,960
the task you assigned.

697
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:28,040
The livestream order volume is too big.

698
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:28,920
Here's what we'll do.

699
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,440
Compile the data for me,

700
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:31,440
how much we can actually produce.

701
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:32,760
I'll ask other factories in our group

702
00:30:32,760 --> 00:30:34,080
to join the cultural product line.

703
00:30:34,360 --> 00:30:35,760
Good, that's exactly what I was thinking.

704
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:37,520
I'll compile the data and report to you right away.

705
00:30:39,360 --> 00:30:40,040
Now this one,

706
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:42,240
our Twelve Beauties of Jinling series,

707
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,160
the twelfth design,

708
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:45,480
and it's our final piece, Huhu.

709
00:30:45,840 --> 00:30:46,600
Huhu here

710
00:30:46,600 --> 00:30:49,080
is the laziest of the twelve sisters.

711
00:30:49,080 --> 00:30:49,760
This is our

712
00:30:49,760 --> 00:30:51,680
limited Twelve Beauties of Jinling piece.

713
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:54,080
Only 1,000 pieces released worldwide.

714
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:55,720
You heard that right, everyone.

715
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:56,360
I see

716
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:58,600
some fans who don't know are still asking,

717
00:30:58,600 --> 00:30:59,840
where can you buy Huhu?

718
00:30:59,840 --> 00:31:00,520
Great question.

719
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:02,280
So let me say it again.

720
00:31:02,320 --> 00:31:05,240
You can't buy it anywhere.

721
00:31:05,280 --> 00:31:06,720
Many of you who already got

722
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:07,880
the limited edition, my dear folks,

723
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,000
you got it through bidding.

724
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:10,000
It's 99 yuan.

725
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:12,760
Today we have a bundle deal in our livestream.

726
00:31:12,760 --> 00:31:14,560
The bundle price for ten blind boxes

727
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:16,320
is 799 yuan.

728
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:17,680
Just 799 yuan.

729
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:20,200
This is our livestream encore special.

730
00:31:20,200 --> 00:31:21,520
Miss this window,

731
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:23,600
and everything returns to original price.

732
00:31:23,920 --> 00:31:24,640
Listen up now.

733
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:25,760
Sister Xin.

734
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:27,040
I just came from the finance department.

735
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:28,280
I've got great news for you.

736
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:29,760
Don't keep me hanging, just tell me.

737
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:31,320
Our current sales revenue

738
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:32,760
has already covered all the costs.

739
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:33,760
We're officially in the black.

740
00:31:33,760 --> 00:31:34,520
Are you ready?

741
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:35,080
Come on, get ready.

742
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:35,760
Excellent.

743
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:37,080
Three, two, one.

744
00:31:37,160 --> 00:31:38,200
Launch the link!

745
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:39,200
Come on, Xiao Xing.

746
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,160
Raise your glass too.

747
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:43,000
Let me say something serious.

748
00:31:43,280 --> 00:31:45,800
I really, really thank the two of you.

749
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:49,640
Deep down, I consider you my saviors.

750
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:51,880
Now you're finally talking sense.

751
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:54,040
Without me and President Xin,

752
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:55,600
you'd right now

753
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:57,720
be back home scooping paper by now.

754
00:31:58,680 --> 00:31:59,680
How should I put it?

755
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:01,000
You'd be nothing.

756
00:32:01,520 --> 00:32:02,280
Absolutely nothing.

757
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,560
Praise you a bit and you get all puffed up.

758
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:04,400
Come on, come on.

759
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:05,440
Let's toast.

760
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:06,760
Cheers.

761
00:32:07,080 --> 00:32:08,000
Thank you, President Xin.

762
00:32:16,760 --> 00:32:17,840
Uncle Xuan Yan

763
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:19,560
I want to go to your place

764
00:32:19,560 --> 00:32:20,920
and see the things you designed

765
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:23,720
Dad says your designer toys are amazing

766
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:25,840
Any one of them is worth 5,000 yuan

767
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:27,800
Right, Dad?

768
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:29,040
Worth 5,000 yuan.

769
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:32,680
Well, they're not all that expensive.

770
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:34,760
I remember your, um, your...

771
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:35,680
figurine

772
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:37,400
was only 99, right?

773
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:38,960
No, no.

774
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:41,360
Ten as a bundle is 799.

775
00:32:42,520 --> 00:32:43,960
That price is reasonable.

776
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:45,480
You're selling them too cheap.

777
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:46,680
At least 2,000.

778
00:32:47,880 --> 00:32:49,600
What are you two talking about?

779
00:32:50,480 --> 00:32:52,840
If Xiao Xing likes them, just grab some.

780
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:53,280
No.

781
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:54,320
Xiao Xing, I'll take you there.

782
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:55,080
No, no, no.

783
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:55,800
That won't do.

784
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:57,280
How could we just take them for free?

785
00:32:57,400 --> 00:32:58,720
No matter what,

786
00:32:58,960 --> 00:32:59,960
these were designed by your Uncle Xuan Yan

787
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:01,480
with a lot of hard work.

788
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:02,560
Right, Xuan Yan?

789
00:33:03,360 --> 00:33:04,080
Two thousand.

790
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,440
Two thousand, worth it.

791
00:33:05,440 --> 00:33:07,280
Worth two thousand, definitely worth it.

792
00:33:07,800 --> 00:33:09,120
Hurry up and take Xiao Xing

793
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:10,480
to see your designer toys.

794
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:11,280
Alright then.

795
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:12,040
Come on, Xiao Xing.

796
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:13,480
Uncle Xuan Yan will take you.

797
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:15,280
Uncle Xuan Yan will personally

798
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:16,520
give you a proper explanation.

799
00:33:16,520 --> 00:33:17,480
This is the perfect time for her to learn.

800
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:19,720
I won't charge your dad for the tour.

801
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:20,520
Here, here.

802
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:21,840
Young entrepreneurs

803
00:33:21,840 --> 00:33:23,760
put in real work, so they deserve to be paid.

804
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:24,480
I'll send you a red envelope.

805
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:27,960
Let's go, Xiao Xing.

806
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,800
That kid is such a handful.

807
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:35,080
You didn't eat much, did you?

808
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:36,680
No, I ate plenty.

809
00:33:38,040 --> 00:33:38,520
Well then,

810
00:33:40,600 --> 00:33:42,920
let's find somewhere quieter

811
00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:43,760
to have a chat.

812
00:33:45,280 --> 00:33:45,960
It's too late.

813
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:46,920
I can't stay up any longer.

814
00:33:48,120 --> 00:33:49,280
The night's still young.

815
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:54,760
So...

816
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:56,600
Is it far?

817
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:57,320
Not far.

818
00:33:57,560 --> 00:33:58,520
Just over there.

819
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:00,720
Just a little chat.

820
00:34:02,280 --> 00:34:03,080
Alright.

821
00:34:05,600 --> 00:34:07,520
Last time I chatted with Xiao Xing,

822
00:34:08,520 --> 00:34:09,840
she said when she grows up,

823
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:11,760
she wants to be a giant African insect.

824
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,520
Kids these days...

825
00:34:16,520 --> 00:34:17,280
Well,

826
00:34:17,679 --> 00:34:19,159
their minds jump around too fast.

827
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:21,080
Today she says she wants to be a big insect,

828
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:22,280
tomorrow it'll be something else.

829
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:23,000
Whatever pops into her head.

830
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:24,400
Don't take it to heart.

831
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:25,480
She's quite adorable.

832
00:34:26,280 --> 00:34:27,199
But Mr. Xiao,

833
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:30,239
you heard it at dinner today.

834
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:31,360
Xiao Xing said

835
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:33,440
she doesn't like you dressing so flashy.

836
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:35,120
That shows Xiao Xing

837
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:36,719
doesn't want to be the center of attention.

838
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:38,520
President Xin,

839
00:34:38,960 --> 00:34:40,280
don't laugh at me, President Xin.

840
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:41,920
Today, in front of the kid,

841
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:42,840
I was too embarrassed to say it.

842
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:44,040
Actually,

843
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:45,159
me dressing

844
00:34:45,159 --> 00:34:46,199
like she described,

845
00:34:46,199 --> 00:34:47,360
with that big chain and all,

846
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:49,080
that's all on purpose.

847
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:54,159
Xiao Xing goes to a boarding school.

848
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:56,840
I'm afraid her classmates would bully her,

849
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:58,280
especially the boys.

850
00:35:01,640 --> 00:35:02,960
It hasn't been easy for you.

851
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:05,040
President Xin,

852
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:08,120
you probably know our family situation.

853
00:35:08,920 --> 00:35:10,200
Xiao Xing is really pitiful.

854
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:11,960
She lost her mother when she was little.

855
00:35:12,680 --> 00:35:14,360
And I'm always busy with work,

856
00:35:14,560 --> 00:35:15,600
so I don't look after her much.

857
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:17,040
On top of that,

858
00:35:17,960 --> 00:35:20,040
my parenting style really has issues.

859
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:22,160
So naturally she won't talk to me.

860
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:24,200
I still want to sincerely ask you,

861
00:35:24,200 --> 00:35:25,640
if you have time,

862
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:26,600
please help me.

863
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:29,320
Take good care of her on my behalf.

864
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:30,680
Spend more time with her, even if...

865
00:35:33,040 --> 00:35:34,120
Don't say that.

866
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:35,640
Actually,

867
00:35:36,440 --> 00:35:38,320
being with Xiao Xing

868
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:42,760
brings me a lot of joy.

869
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:44,320
I really like her.

870
00:35:49,600 --> 00:35:50,360
Yuqing,

871
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:53,920
Xuan Yan mentioned the patent registry.

872
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:55,840
Handle it for him as soon as you can.

873
00:35:57,160 --> 00:35:58,520
Our company's patent registrations

874
00:35:58,520 --> 00:36:00,520
